---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { profile } from "@/settings";
import List from "@/components/ui/List.astro";
import ResearchAreaCards from "@/components/ui/ResearchAreaCards.astro";
import Heading from "@/components/ui/Heading.astro";
import { projects } from "@/data/projects";
---

<Layout title={`About | ${profile.fullName}`}>
	<div class="max-w-none">
		<div class="prose max-w-none">
			<Heading level={1}>About Me</Heading>

			<div class="mb-12">
				<p class="text-lg mb-6">
					I am a Senior Researcher in Trustworthy Systems at the <a
						href="https://www.turing.ac.uk/people/researchers/christopher-burr"
						class="link">Alan Turing Institute</a>. I lead the Innovation and 
						Impact Hub for the <a href="https://www.turing.ac.uk/research/research-projects/tric-dt" class="link" >Turing Research and Innovation Cluster in Digital Twins</a>.
				</p>
				<p class="text-lg mb-6">
					In general, I think of myself as an interdisciplinary researcher
					who is passionate about a wide variety of topics and their intersections. 
					Admittedly, this creates complications in academic circles, as people typically want to place others inside neat departmental boundaries. However, it
					really doesn't do a good job of capturing my interest or
					expertise.
				</p>

				<p class="text-lg mb-6">
					For instance, I enjoy reading philosophy as much as writing
					Python, and detailed data analysis as much as designing skills
					workshops. My curiosity also ranges from empirical studies of
					human decision-making to the complex networks of large language
					models. In short, the following phrase resonates well with how I
					see myself:
				</p>

				<blockquote class="mb-6">
					A jack of all trades is a master of none, but oftentimes better
					than a master of one.
				</blockquote>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Taking the component out of the prose container -->
		<div class="mb-12">
			<Heading level={2}>Research Areas</Heading>
			<ResearchAreaCards columns={3} title="" />
		</div>

		<div class="prose max-w-none">
			<Heading level={2}>Research Impact</Heading>
			<p class="text-lg mb-6">
				I strongly believe that addressing major societal
				challenges requires deep collaboration. As such, my research connects theory
				with practice to achieve tangible and meaningful outcomes. This approach has led to
				direct contributions to public policy, including work featured in the UK
				Department for Science, Innovation, and Technology's (DSIT) <a
					href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/introduction-to-ai-assurance/introduction-to-ai-assurance"
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
					>Introduction to AI Assurance framework</a
				>.
			</p>
			<p class="text-lg mb-6">
				This belief also drives the creation and application of free and open-source resources like
				the <a
					href="https://assuranceplatform.azurewebsites.net/"
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
					>Trustworthy and Ethical Assurance (TEA) Platform</a
				>. This methodology is now integral to major initiatives such as the
				Â£8.8M EPSRC-funded <a
					href="https://cvdnet.org.uk/"
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer">CVD-Net project</a
				>, where I co-lead the work package focused on assurance,
				engagement, and ethics.
				Additionally, the <a
					href="https://alan-turing-institute.github.io/turing-commons/"
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer">Turing Commons</a
				> project I co-founded, provides valuable educational resources for responsible
				innovation as one of two strategic skills project for the Alan Turing Institute's Turing 2.0 strategy.
			</p>
			<p class="text-lg mb-6">
				Furthermore, my work fosters consensus and shared practice within
				key technology domains. This includes leading the Special Interest
				Group on Uncertainty and Trust for the <a
					href="https://dtnetplus.ac.uk/"
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer">UKRI Digital Twin Network+</a
				> and co-authoring influential papers, such as the <a
					href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.14259252"
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
					>Trustworthy and Ethical Assurance of Digital Twins</a
				> report, which was developed collaboratively with several partners and organisations to help operationalise assurance principles
				within the UKs digital twinning community.
			</p>
			<List
				listTitle="Current Projects"
				listItems={projects.filter(project => project.active).map(project => ({
					title: project.title,
					link: project.link,
					description: project.description
				}))}
			/>

			<List
				listTitle="Past Projects"
				listItems={projects.filter(project => !project.active).map(project => ({
					title: project.title,
					link: project.link,
					description: project.description
				}))}
			/>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>